        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43356",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=michael.kues@telenet.be",
                        "name": "michael.kues@telenet.be",
                        "displayName": "Kues Michael",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Tried to reproduce the behavior, but we could not reproduce it.  The comma is ignored (meaning it is not converted to a hex code in _encodeQuotedPrintable) which is the intended behavior.  As stated by the Quoted-printable encoding mechanism, all ASCII codes within the range 33 and 126 should be ignored.  The comma falls within this range with it's ASCII code 44.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=michael.kues@telenet.be",
                        "name": "michael.kues@telenet.be",
                        "displayName": "Kues Michael",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-11-27T05:22:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-11-27T05:22:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43411",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=milehr",
                        "name": "milehr",
                        "displayName": "M Lehr",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "hi michael,\r\n\r\nthanks for your reply.\r\n\r\nyes the comma falls within the range - thats okay.\r\n\r\nI think the problem is in Zend_Mail->_formatAddress.\r\n\r\n{code:php}\r\nprotected function _formatAddress($email, $name)\r\n{\r\n    if ($name === '' || $name === null || $name === $email) {\r\n        return $email;\r\n    } else {\r\n        $encodedName = $this->_encodeHeader($name);\r\n        if ($encodedName === $name &&\r\n                ((strpos($name, '@') !== false) || (strpos($name, ',') !== false))) {\r\n            $format = '\"%s\" <%s>';\r\n        } else {\r\n            $format = '%s <%s>';\r\n        }\r\n        return sprintf($format, $encodedName, $email);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nif $name is set, it will be encoded. So if there is a char which is not in the ASCII range between 33 and 126, this one will be encoded ($encodedName = $this->_encodeHeader($name);)\r\n\r\nBut then, the $name will only be double quoted when $encodedName === $name - but this will result in false if there is a char with ASCII code outside of the range 33-126.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=milehr",
                        "name": "milehr",
                        "displayName": "M Lehr",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-01T08:52:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-01T08:52:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43458",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This would be the correct string, right?\r\n\r\n{code}From: =??Q?The=20rabbit,=20which=20is=20Bernd's=20best=20fr=C3=B6nd!?= <bernd@example.org>{code}",
